On Thursday, May 19, 2005, at 03:51PM, Don Tuleja <durocshark(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:

>Some guys like to leave the exhaust manifolds on during this process.
>The reasoning is that the manifold flanges will help guide the drill
>(and tap) straight.

I've measured the oval manifolds and provide the stud measurements:

http://www.ratwell.com/technical/Exhaust.html

The fit is tight and as Don says if you get the alignment wrong you'll have a difficullt time modifying the HE to seal against the head. Be sure to do one stud at a time and check the fit as you go.

